  "description": "Tesla designs and manufactures electric vehicles and energy systems. The auto lineup spans Model 3, Model Y, Model S, Model X, Cybertruck, and Semi; the Energy segment sells Powerwall, Megapack, and solar. Tesla develops an end\u2011to\u2011end autonomy stack (Autopilot and Full Self\u2011Driving), operates the Supercharger network based on the NACS standard, and is building the Dojo training supercomputer; longer\u2011term initiatives include a robotaxi platform and the Optimus humanoid robot, alongside manufacturing innovations such as 4680 cells and gigacasting. Customers include consumers, commercial fleets, and utilities; competitors include BYD and global automakers (Volkswagen, Toyota, GM, Ford, Hyundai\u2011Kia), EV peers like Rivian and Lucid, autonomy players Waymo and Cruise (and ride\u2011hailing networks Uber and Lyft), and energy\u2011storage providers such as BYD and Fluence. Key suppliers include CATL, Panasonic, and LG Energy Solution (battery cells), NVIDIA (AI accelerators), and TSMC (foundry for custom chips).",
